00:14:30,220 --> 00:14:32,360
Is that why you cut yourself off from everyone?

259
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:33,830
Yeah.Pretty much.

260
00:14:33,830 --> 00:14:35,410
But I don't have a big family.

261
00:14:35,410 --> 00:14:38,100
It's just my brother and sister back in ohio.

262
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:39,200
I don't understand.

263
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:41,420
Wouldn't you want to be close to them now?

264
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:44,080
-Wouldn't you want--
-they don't know.

265
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,780
It's better this way.

266
00:14:45,780 --> 00:14:47,850
I made a clean break.

267
00:14:47,850 --> 00:14:50,300
They don't have to feel sorry for me or worry about me,

268
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:53,350
and I don't have to see all that pity in their eyes.

269
00:14:53,350 --> 00:14:55,990
Doesn't sound fair.

270
00:14:57,070 --> 00:15:02,830
So what's the deal,justin,with you turning everything in your room upside down?

271
00:15:03,810 --> 00:15:08,740
I think I know why,but I can't tell you yet.

272
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:12,440
Look,it seems to me like you have this,I don't know,

273
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:17,710
a pipeline,I guess,into death and wherever it is we go after it.

274
00:15:17,710 --> 00:15:20,330
I probably don't know as much as you think I do.

275
00:15:20,330 --> 00:15:21,840
Just tell me.

276
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:23,740
Do you really talk to the dead?

277
00:15:23,740 --> 00:15:26,530
Do you really help them?

278
00:15:28,130 --> 00:15:29,700
Yeah.

279
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:33,100
Yeah,I do.

280
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:39,640
That's why I'm here.

281
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:42,410
I don't know how,but I was meant to meet you.

282
00:15:42,410 --> 00:15:43,980
Justin,look,I...

283
00:15:43,980 --> 00:15:46,740
I help the dead with their unfinished business.

284
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:50,470
I help them and their loved ones find closure.

285
00:15:50,470 --> 00:15:52,910
Why wait?

286
00:15:52,910 --> 00:15:54,200
You're alive.

287
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:54,800
Right now.

288
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:57,730
Why wouldn't you reach out to the people who love you

289
00:15:57,730 --> 00:16:01,360
so that they can spend time with you while they still can?

290
00:16:01,540 --> 00:16:05,270
I don't need your help with the living.

291
00:16:05,270 --> 00:16:07,420
I need your help with the dead.

292
00:16:07,420 --> 00:16:08,070
What?

293
00:16:08,070 --> 00:16:09,980
After I'm gone...

294
00:16:09,980 --> 00:16:13,280
I need you to help me find someone.

295
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,700
Someone who's dead.

296
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,960
Someone who...

297
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:21,050
may be waiting for me.

298
00:16:31,350 --> 00:16:33,610
Melinda: He seems at peace with it.

299
00:16:33,610 --> 00:16:35,180
Ah,it's a mask.

300
00:16:35,180 --> 00:16:37,290
Deep down,he's probably scared to death.

301
00:16:37,290 --> 00:16:38,070
Maybe.

302
00:16:38,070 --> 00:16:39,310
But I really think he has a plan.

303
00:16:39,310 --> 00:16:41,950
He's thought a lot about it.

304
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:43,500
What are you doing?

305
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:46,390
I'm just trying to scan on this drawing of justin's,

306
00:16:46,390 --> 00:16:49,160
do a search and see if anything comes up.

307
00:16:50,330 --> 00:16:53,390
Yeah,what's that like to know that he could just die at any minute,just like that?

308
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:54,510
I can't imagine.

309
00:16:54,510 --> 00:16:56,940
Well,if you think about it,that's pretty much what we all face.

310
00:16:56,940 --> 00:17:00,310
Ok,true,but you know,we do a pretty good job of pretending it's a long way off,

311
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:01,750
and,well,the odds are on our side.

312
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:02,610
But for justin...

313
00:17:02,610 --> 00:17:07,800
yeah,he's got inside information,and he knows the odds are totally the other way for him.

314
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:08,870
That's gotta be hard.

315
00:17:08,870 --> 00:17:10,500
I mean,would you want to know?

316
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:15,380
If you were gonna die in a month-- Or a week-- Or a year-- Would you?

317
00:17:15,780 --> 00:17:17,360
Yeah.

318
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:19,260
Yeah,I think so.

319
00:17:19,260 --> 00:17:23,450
Say my good-byes,get everything straightened out,prepare.

320
00:17:23,450 --> 00:17:24,230
How about you?

321
00:17:24,230 --> 00:17:26,370
No,I'd want to wake up that morning thinking everything was great.

322
00:17:26,370 --> 00:17:29,450
Have no idea,and then boom,all of a sudden,lights out.

323
00:17:29,450 --> 00:17:31,640
No fears,no regrets,no sadness.

324
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,890
Just happily oblivious until the end.

325
00:17:33,890 --> 00:17:37,420
Ah,happily oblivious,another guy thing.

326
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:39,390
Don't knock it.

327
00:17:39,390 --> 00:17:42,200
Awareness is highly overrated.

328
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:49,740
Wait,this is it.

329
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:52,870
That's what justin drew on my window.

330
00:17:52,870 --> 00:17:55,320
It's the figurehead for a boat.

331
00:17:55,320 --> 00:17:57,480
Who's boat?

332
00:17:59,390 --> 00:18:02,760
witchcraft+boat

333
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:23,270
Woman: I'm waiting for you.

334
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:33,660
Justin.

335
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:37,190
Julie?

336
00:19:50,710 --> 00:19:53,220
I can't believe it's you.

337
00:19:53,220 --> 00:19:55,660
Find me.

338
00:19:58,350 --> 00:19:59,720
Yeah?

339
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:02,380
I'll be waiting.

340
00:20:24,180 --> 00:20:25,320
Justin...

341
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:26,250
melinda.

342
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:28,340
It's perfect.I saw her.

343
00:20:28,340 --> 00:20:29,210
Who?

344
00:20:29,210 --> 00:20:30,140
My girlfriend.

345
00:20:30,140 --> 00:20:31,740
I mean,she was my girlfriend.

346
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:34,370
She's dead,and I saw her.

347
00:20:34,710 --> 00:20:35,360
Where?

348
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:38,940
Here,in this room,and in the mirror.

349
00:20:38,940 --> 00:20:40,390
I mean,I think it's my brain.

350
00:20:40,390 --> 00:20:42,080
This aneurysm,it's letting me see things.

351
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:44,030
Ok,justin,calm down.

352
00:20:45,070 --> 00:20:48,400
was your girlfriend's name julie?

353
00:20:48,890 --> 00:20:50,880
How did you know that?

354
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:53,830
I know what witchcraft means.

355
00:20:53,830 --> 00:20:57,590
I know what the picture you drew means.

356
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,320
How?

357
00:20:59,320 --> 00:21:02,120
You can't hide anything on the 'net.

358
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:04,530
You,of all people,should know that.

359
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:07,400
Tell me what happened.

360
00:21:09,450 --> 00:21:11,440
It was 3 years ago.

361
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:14,320
3 years,2 months and a week.

362
00:21:18,470 --> 00:21:20,400
I was datin' this girl julie.

363
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,900
She was like...

364
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,550
nobody I ever knew.

365
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:26,780
Her family had money,so she could pretty much do whatever she wanted.

366
00:21:26,780 --> 00:21:28,960
They gave her a freakin' vintage boat for christmas,

367
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:32,050
and I'm not talking about the kind in a bottle.

368
00:21:32,050 --> 00:21:35,760
She was wild,totally fearless.

369
00:21:36,560 --> 00:21:38,890
She hung out with this really cool crowd,

370
00:21:38,890 --> 00:21:40,960
but for some reason,she liked me.

371
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:42,710
She said it was because I was smart.

372
00:21:42,710 --> 00:21:43,980
Who knows?

373
00:21:43,980 --> 00:21:46,160
But I loved being around her.

374
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:49,240
It was like you never knew what was going to happen next.

375
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:53,720
Want some?

376
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:55,370
No.

377
00:21:58,920 --> 00:22:02,540
When it became night, she went below to get a sweater,

378
00:22:02,550 --> 00:22:05,730
and she told me to start the engine so we can get home fast.

379
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:20,160
I don't know what happened,

380
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:22,360
but when I went down below to find julie,

381
00:22:22,370 --> 00:22:24,540
the whole boat just flipped...

382
00:22:24,950 --> 00:22:29,380
The keel must have ripped off in the blast, everything was upside down.

383
00:22:50,660 --> 00:22:52,390
I didn't know what to do.

384
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:56,760
I didn't even know how much longer I could hold my breath.

385
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:22,870
Why didn't you ever tell me any of this?

386
00:23:23,030 --> 00:23:24,930
I never told anyone.

387
00:23:26,870 --> 00:23:30,630
I told everyone that I didn't remember anything.

388
00:23:32,030 --> 00:23:34,990
So that's why you've been turning everything upside down?

389
00:23:35,740 --> 00:23:37,590
It's like you're acting out your guilt.

390
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:40,120
Someone else has been acting it out for me.

391
00:23:40,130 --> 00:23:42,670
You may not have had another choice, justin.

392
00:23:42,930 --> 00:23:44,330
Both of you could have died.

393
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:45,800
That would have been better.

394
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:49,520
Better than having to live with this for the last 3 years;

395
00:23:49,630 --> 00:23:51,690
having to see her eyes every night...

396
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:54,380
knowing that she watched me swim away from her.

397
00:23:57,670 --> 00:24:00,480
Dying there would have made things a lot easier.

398
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:04,650
-But you weren't meant to.
-Right.

399
00:24:05,350 --> 00:24:09,170
No, I was meant to hang out and get an aneurysm a couple years later.

400
00:24:09,350 --> 00:24:11,090
Do you think that's your punishment?

401
00:24:11,100 --> 00:24:13,380
I think I was meant to die on that boat.

402
00:24:14,210 --> 00:24:16,160
I was meant to be with julie.

403
00:24:17,450 --> 00:24:20,530
This?It's just a correction.

404
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:22,410
Better late than never.

405
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:25,560
-Justin...
-no, really, it's ok.

406
00:24:25,570 --> 00:24:27,600
I'm totally cool with this.

407
00:24:27,780 --> 00:24:31,720
Besides...I think whatever's waiting for me after I die,

408
00:24:31,730 --> 00:24:34,760
it's going to be a lot more interesting than what I'm leaving behind.

409
00:24:38,040 --> 00:24:39,680
Right, little buddy?

410
00:24:48,310 --> 00:24:50,810
Justin, it's gonna be all right.

411
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:12,150
-Am I...?
-Yes.You're dead.

412
00:25:17,360 --> 00:25:19,870
I totally feel normal, totally alive.

413
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:23,060
Sometimes people don't know what's happening to them at first.

414
00:25:24,110 --> 00:25:27,640
You died in your sleep last night, and that's why you were able to see julie.

415
00:25:27,910 --> 00:25:30,880
Yeah.She told me to find her.

416
00:25:30,890 --> 00:25:34,560
-Where?
-I think I know where.

417
00:25:35,060 --> 00:25:37,980
Justin, you have to go into the light.Ok?

418
00:25:37,990 --> 00:25:40,950
I promise that I will find julie, and I will cross her over.

419
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:45,590
No.She's waiting for me.

420
00:25:47,780 --> 00:25:50,180
-I have to go.
-Now, justin, wait!

421
00:25:58,760 --> 00:25:59,960
Come on.

422
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:03,490
Hey, are you ok?

423
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:04,640
Comparatively speaking.

424
00:26:04,650 --> 00:26:05,270
How are you?

425
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:07,630
I'd feel better if I knew where his spirit was.

426
00:26:09,210 --> 00:26:12,130
-You, uh, talked to him after he...?
-Yeah.

427
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:14,700
He seemed relieved in a way.

428
00:26:14,710 --> 00:26:16,640
I guess it was easier on him then he thought it was going to be.

429
00:26:16,650 --> 00:26:17,930
But he dn'idt want to cross over?

430
00:26:17,940 --> 00:26:21,850
He saw the ghost of his girlfriend, and she told him to come and get her.

431
00:26:21,860 --> 00:26:24,030
That's romantic in a dawn of the dead kind of way.

432
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:25,950
Yeah, he blames himself for her death.

433
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:27,670
And I wouldn't be surprised if she blames him, too.

434
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:29,200
Well, the school notified his next of kin.

435
00:26:29,210 --> 00:26:31,100
It's his brother and sister, they're flying out tonight.

436
00:26:31,110 --> 00:26:32,790
You can find out what they know.

437
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:35,080
Maybe they know something they don't even know they know.

438
00:26:35,190 --> 00:26:36,930
Easy for you to say.

439
00:26:36,940 --> 00:26:38,240
What are you going to do with the rodent?

440
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:39,960
I think you two need each other.

441
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:45,880
Promise I'll be back in an hour.

442
00:27:45,890 --> 00:27:47,400
Will they even talk to you?

443
00:27:47,410 --> 00:27:50,700
Well, since I'm the one who found their brother's body, I guess so.

444
00:27:50,710 --> 00:27:52,890
You know, we could just close up for an hour.

445
00:27:52,900 --> 00:27:53,810
I could go with you.

446
00:27:53,820 --> 00:27:56,220
No, it looks like everybody actually wants to shop today.

447
00:27:56,230 --> 00:27:57,470
I'll be back soon.

448
00:27:58,560 --> 00:28:00,360
Excuse me, how much are these?

449
00:28:00,450 --> 00:28:02,820
Uh, the big ones are 30, the small ones are 20.

450
00:28:02,830 --> 00:28:05,220
They're beautiful.Are they local?

451
00:28:05,490 --> 00:28:07,380
From a mansion in piermont.

452
00:28:07,390 --> 00:28:10,360
There was like 40 or 50 doors.

453
00:28:12,590 --> 00:28:14,060
I have him now.

454
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:15,910
You have to stay out of it.

455
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:18,010
I'm sorry?

456
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:20,670
It was his own free will.

457
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:22,550
There's nothing you can do.

458
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:26,170
Stay away, or I'll have someone burn your house down.

459
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:32,010
Well, that's a lot of doors.

460
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:33,810
Be great for a french farce.

461
00:28:36,970 --> 00:28:39,270
-You ok?
-Yeah.

462
00:28:39,890 --> 00:28:41,640
-Are you?
-Me?

463
00:28:41,650 --> 00:28:43,220
Sure.Fine.

464
00:28:43,230 --> 00:28:46,350
I'm gonna take two of the big ones.

465
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,690
Andy, look.

466
00:29:13,070 --> 00:29:15,850
-Oh, I'm sorry, I can come back.
-No, no, no.

467
00:29:15,860 --> 00:29:19,060
-Did you know justin?
-Well, not very well.

468
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:22,610
But yes.I'm melinda gordon.

469
00:29:22,620 --> 00:29:24,230
You must be his brother and sister.

470
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:25,630
You're the one that found him.

471
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:28,120
Yes.I'm so sorry.

472
00:29:28,670 --> 00:29:30,350
The coroner is telling us it was sudden,

473
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:33,480
but they really don't know yet what happened to justin.

474
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:35,480
Do you know something?

475
00:29:35,580 --> 00:29:37,630
Do you know why our brother died?

476
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:39,640
I know this is really hard to understand.

477
00:29:39,650 --> 00:29:42,050
I'm not sure that I totally do.

478
00:29:42,420 --> 00:29:45,400
But it was really important to him not to be pitied.

479
00:29:45,620 --> 00:29:48,110
He didn't want the two of you to have to grieve.

480
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:49,430
He knew that he was going to die,

481
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:51,210
and there was nothing you could do to change that.

482
00:29:51,220 --> 00:29:52,660
It's just not fair.

483
00:29:52,750 --> 00:29:54,430
Didn't he know that we loved him?

484
00:29:54,440 --> 00:29:55,950
He's the only family we have.

485
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:59,470
If it helps, he seemed really at peace with it.

486
00:29:59,860 --> 00:30:02,220
For him, it was like a journey that he had to take,

487
00:30:02,230 --> 00:30:04,120
that he--he wanted to take.

488
00:30:04,130 --> 00:30:06,290
He just felt like he had to do it alone.

489
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:08,110
Yeah, that sounds like justin.

490
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:10,270
Do you know about the boat thing?

491
00:30:10,930 --> 00:30:12,880
Said he didn't remember what happened on that boat,

492
00:30:12,890 --> 00:30:14,720
but he was never the same after that.

493
00:30:15,040 --> 00:30:19,660
It was like he just withdrew, like he felt he didn't belong here anymore.

494
00:30:19,930 --> 00:30:22,210
What was he like before?

495
00:30:22,970 --> 00:30:28,320
Just...like a curious little boy, with the best heart.

496
00:30:28,900 --> 00:30:30,490
Our parents died when we were pretty young.

497
00:30:30,500 --> 00:30:32,030
Justin was only 10.

498
00:30:32,130 --> 00:30:36,290
He used to save his money, whatever he could get from errands, dog walking,

499
00:30:36,430 --> 00:30:38,800
and he'd buy things for our mom and dad.

500
00:30:39,090 --> 00:30:40,670
But they were dead?

501
00:30:42,850 --> 00:30:45,060
And he would get newspapers that my dad used to read,

502
00:30:45,070 --> 00:30:46,830
and books that my mom would like,

503
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:50,190
and he'd go there and read to them, sit with them for hours.

504
00:30:50,200 --> 00:30:54,030
Bring my dad's favorite snacks, said he didn't want them to be lonely.

505
00:30:54,040 --> 00:30:56,200
He gave up time with his friends.

506
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:58,780
He felt like he couldn't abandon mom and dad.

507
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:01,310
People started calling him the gravesitter.

508
00:31:02,430 --> 00:31:05,800
That'S...that's amazing.

509
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:09,830
It was like he had the weight of the world on his shoulders.

510
00:31:09,890 --> 00:31:13,050
He just...felt things very deeply.

511
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:17,110
Was he happy?When he was with julie?

512
00:31:17,120 --> 00:31:21,480
-He was, I guess.But we weren'T.
-Why not?

513
00:31:21,490 --> 00:31:23,820
She just wasn't anything like justin.

514
00:31:23,900 --> 00:31:25,820
She was a spoiled rich kid.

515
00:31:25,830 --> 00:31:30,320
Hung with a really fast crowd, other rich kids.Bad kids.

516
00:31:30,580 --> 00:31:33,840
That detective thought the whole boat thing was suspicious.

517
00:31:33,850 --> 00:31:35,380
What detective?

518
00:31:56,340 --> 00:31:57,570
